9-1205; Manabe, S., Stouffer, R.J., Spelman, M.J., Bryan, K., Transient responses of a coupled ocean-atmosphere model to gradual changes of atmospheric CO2. Part I: Annual mean response (1991) J. Climate, 4, pp. 785-818; North, G.R., (1996) GPS-CLIM: A Microsatellite Constellation to Test Climate Models, , Proposal to NASA's Earth System Science Path-finder Program, Jet Propulsion Laboratory, California Institute of Technology, 248 pp. [Available from Jet Propulsion Laboratory, California Institute of Technology, Pasadena, CA 91109-8099.]; Kim, K.-Y., Shen, S.S.P., Hardin, J.W., Detection of forced climate signals. Part I: Filter theory (1995) J. Climate, 8, pp. 401-408; Polyak, I., Observed versus simulated second-moment climate statistics in GCM verification problems (1996) J. Atmos. Sci., 53, pp. 677-694; North, G.R., Evaluation of the GFDL GCM climate variability, II: Stochastic modeling and latitude-temporal fields (1997) J. Geophys. Res., 102, pp. 6799-6812; Evaluation of the geophysical fluid dynamics laboratory general-circulation model climate variability, I: Variances and zonal time-series (1997) J. Geophys. Res., 102, pp. 1921-1929; Santer, B.D., Taylor, K.E., Penner, J.E., Wigley, T.M.L., Cubasch, U., Jones, P.D., Towards the detection and attribution of an anthropogenic effect on climate (1995) Climate Dyn., 12, pp. 77-100; Wigley, T.M.L., Barnett, T.P., Anyamba, E., Detection of climate change and attribution of causes (1996) Climate Change 1995: The Science of Climate Change, , J. T. Houghton et al., Eds., Cambridge University Press, 572 pp; A search for human influences on the thermal structure in the atmosphere (1996) Nature, 382, pp. 39-46; Tett, S.F.B., Mitchell, J.F.B., Parker, D.E., Allen, M.R., Human influence on the atmospheric vertical temperature structure - Detection and observations (1996) Science, 274, pp. 1170-1173","Leroy, S.S.; Earth and Space Sciences Division, Jet Propulsion Laboratory, California Institute of Technology, 4800 Oak Gr